From cca6d4d23fce144edc2412754383270e33eea3f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Guillem Jover <guillem@hadrons.org>
Date: Tue, 12 May 2026 06:08:18 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Fix groff warning due to missing hint to run the tbl
 preprocessor

With newer groff versions we are getting the following warning with
lintian:

  groff-message an.tmac:<standard input>:111: warning: tbl preprocessor failed, or it or soelim was not run; table(s) likely not rendered (TE macro called with TW register undefined) [usr/share/man/man8/pcilmr.8.gz:1]

Warned-by: lintian
Origin: vendor
Forwarded: no
---
 pcilmr.man | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/pcilmr.man b/pcilmr.man
index 488ce83..779906d 100644
--- a/pcilmr.man
+++ b/pcilmr.man
@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@
+'\" t
 .TH PCILMR 8 "@TODAY@" "@VERSION@" "The PCI Utilities"
 .SH NAME
 pcilmr \- margin PCIe Links
-- 
2.53.0

